odified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7377","content_id":"1624","tag_id":"150","order":"6","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"7378","content_id":"1624","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"1623","code":"environment-and-the-pan-atlantic-space","user_id":"1","title":"Environment and the Pan-Atlantic Space","abstract":"ATLANTIC FUTURE scientific paper no. 32 is out: \"Regional environmental challenges and solutions in the Pan-Atlantic Space\" by&nbsp;Elizabeth Tedsen and R. Andreas Kraemer at&nbsp;Ecologic Institute","body":"<p>The pan-Atlantic is not an abstract of international relations, but is a&nbsp;biophysical reality. We examine the Atlantic-specific, regional&nbsp;dynamics of global environmental challenges and solutions,&nbsp;considering whether the interconnected Atlantic space helps to&nbsp;resolve, or instead worsens, these and how the natural and human&nbsp;linkages within the Atlantic Basin intersect in regional governance.&nbsp;The pan-Atlantic and its sub-structures are found to be useful units of&nbsp;analysis for understanding and addressing environmental challenges.&nbsp;Beyond a shared physical environment, Atlantic countries also share&nbsp;common histories and starting points, which may serve as the basis&nbsp;for inter-Basin cooperation in resource management challenges<\/p>","views":"166","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":false,"type":"0","created":"2015-12-09 11:04:00","modified":"2016-02-02 08:51:52"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"186","content_id":"1623","type":"1","file_name":"1623-Regional environmental challenges and solutions in the Pan-Atlantic Space.pdf","description":"Regional environmental challenges and solutions in the Pan-Atlantic Space","created":"2015-12-09 11:06:58","modified":"2015-12-09 11:06:58"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"7371","content_id":"1623","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},{"id":"7366","content_id":"1623","tag_id":"1","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"1","code":"atlantic-basin","name":"Atlantic Basin","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 09:54:32","modified":"2013-09-27 09:54:32"}},{"id":"7367","content_id":"1623","tag_id":"109","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"109","code":"environment","name":"Environment","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:06:53","modified":"2013-09-27 11:06:53"}},{"id":"7368","content_id":"1623","tag_id":"155","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"155","code":"regionalism","name":"Regionalism","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2014-01-10 12:59:30","modified":"2014-01-10 12:59:30"}},{"id":"7369","content_id":"1623","tag_id":"126","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"126","code":"cooperation","name":"Cooperation","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-30 10:21:56","modified":"2013-09-30 10:21:56"}},{"id":"7370","content_id":"1623","tag_id":"150","order":"5","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"7371","content_id":"1623","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"1602","code":"a-two-centuries-overview-of-the-atlantic","user_id":"1","title":"A two centuries overview of the Atlantic","abstract":"ATLANTIC FUTURE scientific paper no. 27 is out: \"Historical Power Relations and changes in the Atlantic: a two centuries overview\" by&nbsp;Nuno Severiano Teixeira and&nbsp;Daniel Marcos at&nbsp;IPRI-NOVA","body":"<p>This paper identifies the most important political turning points in the Atlantic <br \/>history from the end of the 18th century until the present day. Based on a <br \/>chronological approach, we have selected a series of historical events that <br \/>affected the Atlantic area and changed its power relations in the last two <br \/>centuries. With this analysis, we are able to identify the points of contact, <br \/>interaction and differentiation between the various shores that bring together <br \/>the Atlantic area, concluding that, despite some periods of greater <br \/>detachment, the Atlantic may become a larger political, economic and <br \/>security community.<\/p>","views":"102","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":false,"type":"0","created":"2015-12-03 14:55:00","modified":"2016-02-06 11:16:45"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"185","content_id":"1602","type":"1","file_name":"1602-Historical Power Relations and changes in the Atlantic. A two centuries overview.pdf","description":"Historical Power Relations and changes in the Atlantic: a two centuries overview","created":"2015-12-03 15:02:23","modified":"2015-12-03 15:02:23"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"7365","content_id":"1602","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},{"id":"7361","content_id":"1602","tag_id":"152","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"152","code":"instituto-portugues-de-relaces-internacionais-ipri","name":"Instituto Portugu\u00eas de Rela\u00e7\u00f5es Internacionais (IPRI)","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-10 14:59:43","modified":"2013-12-10 14:59:43"}},{"id":"7362","content_id":"1602","tag_id":"7","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"7","code":"power","name":"Power","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 10:05:06","modified":"2013-09-27 10:05:06"}},{"id":"7363","content_id":"1602","tag_id":"147","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"147","code":"international-relations","name":"international relations","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-11-18 11:32:59","modified":"2013-11-18 11:32:59"}},{"id":"7364","content_id":"1602","tag_id":"150","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"7365","content_id":"1602","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"1601","code":"atlantic-eclectic-but-converging-region","user_id":"1","title":"Atlantic: eclectic but converging region?","abstract":"ATLANTIC FUTURE scientific paper no. 30 is out: \"The Atlantic Basin: An eclectic but converging region?\" by&nbsp;Giovanni Grevi at Fundaci&oacute;n para las Relaciones Internacionales y el Di&aacute;logo Exterior (FRIDE)","body":"<p>The Atlantic Basin receives less attention from international relations experts <br \/>than other maritime spaces around the world, such as the Mediterranean <br \/>Sea, the Arctic Circle, the Indian Ocean or the Asia-Pacific. This is probably, <br \/>at least in part, because this enormous geopolitical area &ndash; including <br \/>countries from North America, Central America, Europe as well as littoral <br \/>countries in South America and Africa - is very eclectic. However, the vast <br \/>majority of the countries that form the Atlantic basin are democracies, and <br \/>collectively they account for the majority of global trade and foreign <br \/>investment as well as a very large and growing proportion of energy <br \/>resources. In addition, the absence of entrenched rivalry among the main <br \/>powers of the Atlantic Basin is notable compared to the hardening <br \/>geopolitics of other regions. This FRIDE working paper highlights some of <br \/>the principal dimensions of interdependence within the Atlantic Basin - such <br \/>as trade, investment and energy - as well as the main political and security <br \/>trends therein. It shows that intra-Atlantic links and common challenges are <br \/>growing, but also that connections between Atlantic countries and Asia, <br \/>notably China, are fast expanding. On that basis, the paper assesses the <br \/>prospects for future cooperation across this massive maritime space.<\/p>","views":"154","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":false,"type":"0","created":"2015-12-03 13:54:00","modified":"2016-02-08 05:31:08"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"184","content_id":"1601","type":"1","file_name":"1601-The Atlantic Basin. An eclectic but converging region.pdf","description":"The Atlantic Basin: an eclectic but converging region?","created":"2015-12-03 14:41:56","modified":"2015-12-03 14:41:56"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"7360","content_id":"1601","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},{"id":"7356","content_id":"1601","tag_id":"1","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"1","code":"atlantic-basin","name":"Atlantic Basin","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 09:54:32","modified":"2013-09-27 09:54:32"}},{"id":"7357","content_id":"1601","tag_id":"121","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"121","code":"interdependence","name":"Interdependence","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 13:12:07","modified":"2013-09-27 13:12:07"}},{"id":"7358","content_id":"1601","tag_id":"151","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"151","code":"fundacion-para-las-relaciones-internacionales-y-el-dialogo-exterior-fride","name":"Fundaci\u00f3n para las Relaciones Internacionales y el Di\u00e1logo Exterior (FRIDE)","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-10 14:59:23","modified":"2013-12-10 14:59:23"}},{"id":"7359","content_id":"1601","tag_id":"150","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"7360","content_id":"1601","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"1600","code":"an-emerging--globalised-atlantic-space","user_id":"1","title":"An emerging & globalised Atlantic Space?","abstract":"ATLANTIC FUTURE scientific paper no. 31 is out: \"An emerging and globalised Atlantic Space?\", by&nbsp;Jordi Vaquer, Laia Tarragona and Pol Morillas Barcelona at Centre for International Affairs (CIDOB) ","body":"<p>While the Atlantic has lost the pre-eminence of times past, it is still an essential part of today&rsquo;s globalised world. This article gives an overview of the defining features of globalisation and looks at the shortcomings of global governance in the ongoing shift of power. The article analyses some of the challenges for the emergence of a wider Atlantic space. Failure to unite all regions bordering the Atlantic into a common view, the scepticism in South Atlantic countries about the very idea of the Atlantic space, the lack of efficient management of common and scarce resources, the food imbalances found in the Atlantic and the issues that come with state fragility are analysed here as some of the main obstacles to the emergence of a true Atlantic space based on cooperation and opportunities for all the regions. Finally, the paper concludes with a reflection on the potential for cooperation in the Atlantic in certain specific areas.<\/p>","views":"181","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":false,"type":"0","created":"2015-12-03 13:11:00","modified":"2016-02-07 14:27:49"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"189","content_id":"1600","type":"1","file_name":"1600-WP1_CIDOB_An emerging and globalised Atlantic Space.pdf","description":"An emerging and globalised Atlantic Space? ","created":"2015-12-14 18:57:01","modified":"2015-12-14 18:57:01"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"7351","content_id":"1600","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},{"id":"7347","content_id":"1600","tag_id":"6","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"6","code":"globalisation","name":"Globalisation","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 10:03:52","modified":"2013-09-27 10:03:52"}},{"id":"7348","content_id":"1600","tag_id":"88","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"88","code":"governance","name":"Governance","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 10:55:35","modified":"2013-09-27 10:55:35"}},{"id":"7349","content_id":"1600","tag_id":"46","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"46","code":"barcelona-centre-for-international-affairs-cidob","name":"Barcelona Centre for International Affairs (CIDOB)","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-02 14:29:22","modified":"2013-12-02 14:29:22"}},{"id":"7350","content_id":"1600","tag_id":"150","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"7351","content_id":"1600","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"1599","code":"atlantic-business-briefs","user_id":"1","title":"Atlantic business briefs","abstract":"Business briefs&nbsp;Economic and financial links in the Atlantic Space by&nbsp;Mark Aspinwall, Centro de Investigaci&oacute;n y Docencia Econ&oacute;micas A.C. (CIDE) and&nbsp;Outlook for the Fossil Fuel and Renewable Energy Industries in the Wider Atlantic Space by&nbsp;Christoph H. Stefes and R. Andreas Kraemer Ecologic Institute Berlin","body":"<p><em>Economic and financial links <\/em>are strong across the Atlantic space, especially the North Atlantic. While North-South and South-South links are growing, they are influenced by the presence of external factors, like China or the price of commodities. There is strong evidence of continued and lasting economic interaction among the developed Atlantic in the north, and there does appear to be some trend toward the integration of Africa and Latin America into the Atlantic (and global) trade and investment regimes, through their northern partners, partly because of the rise of emerging market economies (especially Brazil, Mexico, and South Africa) and partly because of decisions to increase South-South economic interactions.<\/p>\r\n<p><em>Fossil Fuel and Renewable Energy Industries<\/em> explains that although, the Atlantic Space holds a large share of the world&rsquo;s unexploited fossil fuel reserves, including 40% of oil reserves, 20% of natural gas reserves, and roughly 40% of coal reserves (BP 2015), the future of the industry is uncertain. Large profit margins (in the past) and continued subsides have made some of these unconventional and difficult hydrocarbon reserves easier to access via new technologies, particularly in the cases of the North Atlantic shale revolution and the Southern Atlantic &ldquo;oil ring&rdquo; ( Isbell 2014). In the North Atlantic, shale gas now accounts for more than 35% of American gas production, compared to 2% in 2000. Demand for shale oil and gas is predicted to rise from 1.96 BCM\/day to 2.69 BCM\/day by 2035 (Szalai 2013). In the Southern Atlantic oil ring, deep-water offshore oil rigs now span from Namibia and Morocco in the east to Argentina and the Gulf of Mexico (Isbell 2014), but their further expansion is in doubt given current and projected oil prices.<\/p>","views":"378","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2015-12-03 12:16:00","modified":"2016-02-08 11:52:48"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","