ternacionais-UNL (IPRI) in Lisbon, Portugal, from 22 to 24 April 2015.\r\n&nbsp;","body":"<p>A public event will be held on the first day under the theme &ldquo;Setting the Grounds for a New Understanding of the Atlantic: Perspectives on current events&rdquo;.<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>The three day event will provide an opportunity for the ATLATIC FUTURE Consortium to meet and discuss the results of the research, review the progress of the Project and to discuss next steps. All partners will be present as well as members of the Scientific and Advisory Panel.<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>This event is&nbsp;<strong>by invitation only<\/strong>.<\/p>\r\n<p>You can follow the Public Session &ldquo;Setting the Grounds for a New Understanding of the Atlantic&rdquo; of April 22nd at the following link:&nbsp; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.ipri.pt\/eventos\/evento.php?ide=202\">http:\/\/www.ipri.pt\/eventos\/evento.php?ide=202<\/a><\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>","views":"372","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":false,"type":"1","created":"2015-03-11 14:15:00","modified":"2016-02-08 11:49:04"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":"477","datetime":"2015-04-22 14:13:00","country":"Portugal","city":"Lisbon","address":"","map":""},"Resource":[{"id":"119","content_id":"477","type":"1","file_name":"477-Setting the grounds for a new understanding of the Atlantic.pdf","description":"Setting the Grounds for a new understanding of the Atlantic","created":"2015-04-20 10:25:36","modified":"2015-04-20 10:25:36"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"5106","content_id":"477","tag_id":"20","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"20","code":"economy-and-finance","name":"Economy and finance","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"A85CA0","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-09-27 09:57:02"}},{"id":"5103","content_id":"477","tag_id":"36","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"36","code":"events","name":"Events","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"995B31","created":"2013-09-27 09:58:37","modified":"2013-09-27 09:58:37"}},{"id":"5104","content_id":"477","tag_id":"152","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"152","code":"instituto-portugues-de-relaces-internacionais-ipri","name":"Instituto Portugu\u00eas de Rela\u00e7\u00f5es Internacionais (IPRI)","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-10 14:59:43","modified":"2013-12-10 14:59:43"}},{"id":"5105","content_id":"477","tag_id":"246","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"246","code":"lisbon","name":"lisbon","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"5106","content_id":"477","tag_id":"20","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"20","code":"economy-and-finance","name":"Economy and finance","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"A85CA0","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-09-27 09:57:02"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"476","code":"webinar-ttip-and-the-wider-atlantic-","user_id":"1","title":"WEBINAR: TTIP AND THE WIDER ATLANTIC ","abstract":"&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\nATLANTIC FUTURE is pleased to invite you to a webinar on the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (TTIP) to be conducted by Dan Hamilton, Director of the Center for Transatlantic Relations at the Paul H. Nitze School of Advanced International Studies (SAIS), Johns Hopkins University.","body":"<p>The Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (TTIP) currently under negotiation by the US and the EU is supported by some and criticised by others. Undoubtedly, it would have a considerable impact on the North Atlantic but not only, as its implications would go beyond and affect all other regions in the world. In the framework of the Atlantic Future project, Dan Hamilton will explore what impact the TTIP will have on the four shores of the wider Atlantic Space. Tim Ridout at the German Marshall Fund of the United States will serve as a discussant.&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Time: 10:00 EDT \/ 16:00 CET &nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;The webinar has now been scheduled as a <strong>Google Hangout on Air<\/strong>. To view it, please follow this link:&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/plus.google.com\/events\/crll6tii09albrrn14on7o66vjc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow nofollow\">https:\/\/plus.google.com\/<wbr \/>events\/<wbr \/>crll6tii09albrrn14on7o66vjc<\/a><br \/><br \/><strong>Ask questions:<\/strong> You can post questions prior or during the event. However, note that you need to have a Google+ profile or a Gmail address. Questions will appear on the right side of the screen, which is where you can submit your questions as well. Simply click &ldquo;Ask a new question!&rdquo; and the moderator will see it.&nbsp;<br \/>If you do not have a Gmail account or Google+ profile, you can ask them ahead of time by just emailing your questions to ltarragona@cidob.org&nbsp;<br \/><br \/><strong>Requirements:<\/strong> You only need high speed Internet connection (please note that Explorer does not always work. This is why we advise you to use Google Chrome).<\/p>\r\n<p>For more information, please send an e-mail to: <a href=\"mailto:ltarragona@cidob.org\">ltarragona@cidob.org<\/a><\/p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>","views":"1255","shares":"1","tweets":"4","mails":"1","published":true,"image":true,"featured":false,"type":"1","created":"2015-03-11 10:00:00","modified":"2016-02-07 07:33:10"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":"476","datetime":"2015-04-15 10:00:00","country":"United States","city":"Washington","address":"","map":""},"Resource":[],"ContentTag":[{"id":"5077","content_id":"476","tag_id":"20","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"20","code":"economy-and-finance","name":"Economy and finance","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"A85CA0","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-09-27 09:57:02"}},{"id":"5076","content_id":"476","tag_id":"36","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"36","code":"events","name":"Events","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"995B31","created":"2013-09-27 09:58:37","modified":"2013-09-27 09:58:37"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"5077","content_id":"476","tag_id":"20","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"20","code":"economy-and-finance","name":"Economy and finance","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"A85CA0","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-09-27 09:57:02"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"469","code":"roundtable-atlantic-drivers-of-change","user_id":"1","title":"Roundtable. Atlantic: Drivers of change","abstract":"\r\n\r\n\r\nBrussels\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOn Feb.&nbsp;24, 2015, the German Marshall Fund of the United States (GMF)&nbsp;Brussels office, in collaboration with the Barcelona Center for International Affairs (CIDOB), the Ecologic Institute, Aberystwyth University, and the Foundation for International Relations and External Dialogue (FRIDE)&nbsp;co-hosted a roundtable discussion&nbsp;on new perspectives on the Atlantic space. Entitled&nbsp;&ldquo;The Atlantic: Drivers of Change&rdquo;, the event took place within a three-year collaborative research project funded by the European Commission under the Seventh Framework Programme, entitled &ldquo;Towards an Atlantic area? Mapping trends, perspectives and interregional dynamics between Europe, Africa and the Americas.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","body":"<p>The discussion kicked&nbsp;off with short presentations on new research findings which analyzed&nbsp;the changes occurring in the Atlantic basin with respect to energy, maritime security, and economic governance. It was argued that there is a high degree of fragmentation within the Atlantic space due to the&nbsp;growing importance of new actors and agendas. While opportunities and challenges exist when it comes to regional cooperation, there was a general consensus that there is a need for integrated&nbsp;policy strategies.<\/p>\r\n<p>Countries along the Atlantic basin have strong bases for&nbsp;cooperation -&nbsp;including language, democratic institutions, and cultural proximity -&nbsp;which are all driving factors for cooperation in the Atlantic. It was noted that a new era of energy may be found in the pan-Atlantic space, as it has the potential to drive the future of energy with its large capacity vis-&agrave;-vis renewable energy. With the expansion of new energy infrastructures in the pan-Atlantic space, this could also lead to market development as it has already caught the attention of Chinese and Indian investments.&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>On maritime security, the discussion highlighted key&nbsp;threats; drug trafficking, organised crime, and piracy, all of&nbsp;which are becoming increasingly interlinked. Governments in both the South and the&nbsp;North see these threats as obstacles for cooperation but have not been able to adequately address the threat, which also carries economic costs for surrounding countries. Therefore,&nbsp;importance of cooperation to cope with maritime security issues was stressed.<\/p>\r\n<p>The discussion concluded with a discussion on the impact of the pending Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (TTIP), which was seen as vital in &nbsp;respect to the way the world is developing. Concerns were also raised about Europe and the U.S. becoming global economic leaders and to what degree they would provide a regulatory framework for others to follow &ndash; or whether some countries may be excluded.<\/p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.flickr.com\/\/photos\/56747675@N07\/sets\/72157650592711037\/show\/\">https:\/\/www.flickr.com\/\/photos\/56747675@N07\/sets\/72157650592711037\/show\/<\/a><\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Text and Photo Courtesy of The German Marshall Fund.<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>","views":"278","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2015-02-27 13:41:00","modified":"2016-02-08 13:29:33"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[],"ContentTag":[{"id":"4846","content_id":"469","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},{"id":"4837","content_id":"469","tag_id":"157","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"157","code":"german-marshall-fund","name":"german marshall fund","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"4838","content_id":"469","tag_id":"46","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"46","code":"barcelona-centre-for-international-affairs-cidob","name":"Barcelona Centre for International Affairs (CIDOB)","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-02 14:29:22","modified":"2013-12-02 14:29:22"}},{"id":"4839","content_id":"469","tag_id":"124","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"124","code":"ecologic-institute-gmbh-ecologic","name":"Ecologic Institute GmbH (ECOLOGIC)","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-02 14:28:09","modified":"2013-12-02 14:28:09"}},{"id":"4840","content_id":"469","tag_id":"151","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"151","code":"fundacion-para-las-relaciones-internacionales-y-el-dialogo-exterior-fride","name":"Fundaci\u00f3n para las Relaciones Internacionales y el Di\u00e1logo Exterior (FRIDE)","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-10 14:59:23","modified":"2013-12-10 14:59:23"}},{"id":"4841","content_id":"469","tag_id":"165","order":"5","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"165","code":"aberystwyth-university-wales-uk","name":"Aberystwyth University Wales (UK)","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2014-01-15 10:50:33","modified":"2014-01-15 10:50:33"}},{"id":"4842","content_id":"469","tag_id":"147","order":"6","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"147","code":"international-relations","name":"international relations","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-11-18 11:32:59","modified":"2013-11-18 11:32:59"}},{"id":"4843","content_id":"469","tag_id":"138","order":"7","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"138","code":"europe","name":"Europe","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:16:35","modified":"2013-10-25 10:16:35"}},{"id":"4844","content_id":"469","tag_id":"140","order":"8","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"140","code":"africa","name":"Africa","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:20:33","modified":"2013-10-25 10:20:33"}},{"id":"4845","content_id":"469","tag_id":"143","order":"9","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"143","code":"america","name":"America","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:41:45","modified":"2013-10-25 10:41:45"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"4846","content_id":"469","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"463","code":"the-atlantic-drivers-of-change-","user_id":"1","title":"THE ATLANTIC: DRIVERS OF CHANGE ","abstract":"GMF,&nbsp;CIDOB, FRIDE, ECOLOGIC INSTITUTE and Aberystwyth&nbsp;University are&nbsp;pleased to invite you to a roundtable discussion on:\r\nThe Atlantic: Drivers of Change\r\nTuesday,&nbsp;February 24, 2015\r\n10:00 - 12:30\r\nA networking lunch will follow the event","body":"<h5>&nbsp;<\/h5>\r\n<p><strong>Welcome remarks<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p>Ian O. Lesser, Executive Director, GMF Transatlantic Center, Brussels; Senior Director, Foreign and Security Policy, The German Marshall Fund of the United States<\/p>\r\n<p>Jordi Bacaria, Director, CIDOB; Atlantic Future Scientific Coordinator<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Speakers<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p>R. Andreas Kraemer, Director Emeritus, Ecologic Institute<\/p>\r\n<p>Elina Viilup, Policy Analyst, DG External Policies, European Parliament's General Secretariat<\/p>\r\n<p>Sangeeta Khorana, Senior Lector in Economics, Aberystwyth University<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Comments by<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p>Vasco Cal, European Commission, ex-BEPA<\/p>\r\n<p>Giovanni Grevi, Director, FRIDE<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Moderator<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p>Anna Ayuso, Senior Researcher,&nbsp;CIDOB&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Location<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p>Brussels office of the German Marshall Fund, Residence Palace, 8th floor, Rue de la Loi 155, 1040 Brussels <em>(Please take the elevator on the left-hand side behind the lobby)<\/em><\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>As Europe and the EU continue to face internal and external policy challenges, the traditional transatlantic space has developed and expanded into a wider Atlantic space. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/sites-gmf.vuturevx.com\/email_handler.aspx?sid=959ed72a-8485-4418-82ec-8e1e89e4b6d0&amp;redirect=http%3a%2f%2fwww.atlanticfuture.eu%2f\">Atlantic Future<\/a>&nbsp;project provides some new perspectives on the Atlantic space as well as presents some of the key policy issues indicated in the project that affect Europe and the EU.<\/p>\r\n<p>The aim of the Atlantic Future is to study the rationales of cooperation in the Atlantic area. It will also suggest strategies for how the EU&nbsp;can engage with the wider transatlantic relationship in the context of the ongoing redistribution of power and the overall rebalancing of relations around and within the Atlantic space.<\/p>\r\n<p>This conversation&nbsp;will explore what economic and geostrategic implications the energy revolution in the Atlantic will&nbsp;entail for regional integration and what kind of regional cooperation could be pursued in order to tackle international security challenges. We will examine the proliferations of trade agreements in the Atlantic, &ldquo;barriers&rdquo; or &ldquo;building blocks&rdquo; for new models of governance in the region, and finally what the role of the European Union in the Atlantic region should&nbsp;be.<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Please confirm your attendance to <a href=\"mailto:bmedroa@gmfus.org\">bmedroa@gmfus.org<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/463-1424259344.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/><\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>The research leading to these results has received funding from the European Union Seventh Framework Programme under the grant agreement n&deg; [320091].<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"tab-image-container\"><img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/463-1424353239.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/463-1424353259.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/463-1424353325.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/><\/p>\r\n<p class=\"tab-image-container\"><img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/463-1424353650.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img class=\"tab-image\" style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 21.9200000762939px;\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/463-1424353854.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/><\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"tab-image-container\">&nbsp;<\/p>","views":"211","shares":"0","tweets":"2","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"1","created":"2015-02-24 10:00:00","modified":"2016-02-06 16:07:05"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":"463","datetime":"2015-02-24 10:00:00","country":"Belgium","city":"Brussels","address":"","map":""},"Resource":[],"ContentTag":[{"id":"5026","content_id":"463","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},{"id":"5021","content_id":"463","tag_id":"137","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"137","code":"european-union","name":"European Union","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:16:06","modified":"2013-10-25 10:16:06"}},{"id":"5022","content_id":"463","tag_id":"5","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"5","code":"atlantic-space","name":"Atlantic space","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 09:55:08","modified":"2013-09-27 09:55:08"}},{"id":"5023","content_id":"463","tag_id":"24","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"24","code":"political-relations","name":"Political relations","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 10:04:54","modified":"2013-09-27 10:04:54"}},{"id":"5024","content_id":"463","tag_id":"147","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"147","code":"international-relations","name":"international relations","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-11-18 11:32:59","modified":"2013-11-18 11:32:59"}},{"id":"5025","content_id":"463","tag_id":"36","order":"5","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"36","code":"events","name":"Events","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"995B31","created":"2013-09-27 09:58:37","modified":"2013-09-27 09:58:37"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"5026","content_id":"463","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"1110","code":"policy-brief-on-energy-in-the-atlantic","user_id":"1","title":"Policy brief on energy in the Atlantic","abstract":"Profound changes are taking place in the area of energy that are transforming the strategic outlook for the Atlantic Basin. These are redrawing global energy maps and moving the global centre of gravity for energy supply westward.","body":"<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Photo: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.flickr.com\/photos\/freefoto\/\">Ian Britton<\/a><\/p>\r\n<p>One of the most exciting &ndash; and potentially most promising &ndash; changes in the Atlantic Basin is the emergence of the Atlantic energy system. The new position for the Atlantic in global energy markets is supported by the shift for demand to emerging Asia-Pacific markets, as well as structural declines in energy demand within the Atlantic Space. The shale revolution, advances in petroleum technology and exploration, as well as movement towards low-carbon economies present new opportunities, interdependencies and perspectives for all Atlantic actors but particularly for the EU to diversify its energy resources.<\/p>\r\n<\/td>\r\n<\/tr>\r\n<\/tbody>\r\n<\/table>","views":"31","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":false,"type":"0","created":"2015-02-20 10:33:00","modified":"2016-01-11 02:41:16"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"148","content_id":"1110","type":"1","file_name":"1110-ATLANTIC FUTURE_ Policy Brief_The changing energy landscape in the Atlantic region.pdf","description":"","created":"2015-09-08 10:33:28","modified":"2015-09-08 10:33:28"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"7391","content_id":"1110","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},{"id":"7389","content_id":"1110","tag_id":"108","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"108","code":"energy","name":"Energy","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:04:45","modified":"2013-09-27 11:04:45"}},{"id":"7390","content_id":"1110","tag_id":"150","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"7391","content_id":"1110","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"1109","code":"policy-brief-on-maritime-security","user_id":"1","title":"Policy brief on maritime security","abstract":"The Atlantic Basin has over the recent decades been considered a relatively pacific zone in military terms. However, non-traditional security concerns are growing. &nbsp;","body":"<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>The Atlantic Basin concentrates some of the main routes for drug trafficking in the world. The availability of drugs and arms is very significant in the Americas, but drug cartels are also developing illegal activities in some West African countries with fragile institutions. Additionally, the Gulf of Guinea is emerging as the hotspot of pirate attacks in the Atlantic. Trafficking in arms, drugs, people and money are common challenges in the Atlantic Space that present important risks but also an opportunity to increased international cooperation across the Basin.<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Download the policy brief here<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<\/td>\r\n<\/tr>\r\n<\/tbody>\r\n<\/table>","views":"24","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":false,"type":"0","created":"2015-02-20 10:28:00","modified":"2016-02-07 16:33:10"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"147","content_id":"1109","type":"1","file_name":"1109-ATLANTIC FUTURE_ Policy Brief_ Maritime security in the Atlantic.pdf","description":"","created":"2015-09-08 10:29:11","modified":"2015-09-08 10:29:11"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"7398","content_id":"1109","tag_id":"21","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"21","code":"security","name":"Security","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"C31F4A","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:37"}},{"id":"7392","content_id":"1109","tag_id":"21","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"21","code":"security","name":"Security","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"C31F4A","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:37"}},{"id":"7393","content_id":"1109","tag_id":"208","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"208","code":"maritime-security","name":"maritime security","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7394","content_id":"1109","tag_id":"260","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"260","code":"policy-brief","name":"policy brief","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7395","content_id":"1109","tag_id":"261","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"261","code":"gulf-of-guinea","name":"gulf of guinea","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7396","content_id":"1109","tag_id":"211","order":"5","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"211","code":"illicit-trafficking","name":"illicit trafficking","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7397","content_id":"1109","tag_id":"150","order":"6","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"7398","content_id":"1109","tag_id":"21","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"21","code":"security","name":"Security","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"C31F4A","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:37"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"450","code":"atlantic-future-seminar-in-rio-de-janeiro","user_id":"1","title":"Atlantic Future Seminar in Rio de Janeiro","abstract":"The second plenary meeting of the ATLANTIC FUTURE project was held in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, from 22 to 24 October 2014. Funda&ccedil;&atilde;o Get&uacute;lio Vargas (FGV) hosted it and representatives of the entire consortium attended to the event. The first day of the meeting consisted of a public event about security issues in the Atlantic region that was held at the Auditorium Engenheiro M. F. Thompson Motta of the Funda&ccedil;&atilde;o Get&uacute;lio Vargas headquarters.\r\n&nbsp;","body":"<p>The public seminar was opened by <strong>Mr. Carlos Iven Simonsen Leal<\/strong>, President of the Funda&ccedil;&atilde;o Get&uacute;lio Vargas, who welcomed the participants and started the seminar by analysing the strategic importance of the Atlantic area and its relationship with international actors such as Asia, the United States of America and the European Union.<\/p>\r\n<p>After that, <strong>Mr. Jordi Bacaria<\/strong>, Director of the Barcelona Centre for Foreign Affairs (CIDOB) explained to the audience the objectives of the ATLANTIC FUTURE project, its achievements during the first period of the project, the future challenges that lay ahead and how global changes are shaping the strategic movements in the region.<\/p>\r\n<p>The seminar continued with a presentation by <strong>Admiral &Aacute;lvaro Augusto Dias Monteiro<\/strong>, President of the Council of the Centre of Political-Strategic Studies of the Brazilian Naval War College, who explained which is the Brazilian Navy's approach to the strategic challenges in the Atlantic area. During his intervention the Admiral mentioned that Brazil has a lack of sources of power which makes necessary to prioritize the strategic way to withstand to traditional and non-traditional threats (maritime crime, rivalry of resources, etc.) that have an impact on the Atlantic sea. According to him, the international security context in which the Atlantic interconnections are developing have induced the Brazilian Navy to think and act in terms of dissuasion by denial or punishment as a way to face the conventional or non-conventional threats that makes the Atlantic Sea a strategically area for the country. Up to the point that the Brazilian Navy has decided to invest in the construction of the Nuclear Submarine for the Brazilian Navy.<\/p>\r\n<p>The Admiral's presentation was followed by three sessions dedicated to the analysis of the &ldquo;the global security order and its impact on the Atlantic regional dynamics&rdquo;, &ldquo;the view of the Atlantic Basin as a security area&rdquo; and &ldquo;the Atlantic security as a path to development&rdquo;. These sessions counted with the participation of different partners of the project and some of them were chaired by special invitees such as the Brazilian Captain Alves de Almeida and Victor Borges (member of the Atlantic Future Scientific Panel). Finally, the seminar closed with a roundtable where participants shared views about how the Atlantic has been changing in terms of past alliances and future prospects for the region.<\/p>\r\n<p>Check photos of the Second Plenary Meeting below:<\/p>\r\n<p class=\"tab-image-container\"><img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/450-1422438518.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/450-1422438592.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/><\/p>\r\n<p class=\"tab-image-container\"><img class=\"tab-image\" style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 21.9200000762939px;\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/450-1422438893.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/><\/p>\r\n<p class=\"tab-image-container\"><img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/450-1422438963.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>&nbsp;&nbsp;<img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/450-1422439389.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/><\/p>\r\n<p class=\"tab-image-container\"><img class=\"tab-image\" src=\"..\/..\/..\/..\/images\/contents\/450-1422439991.jpg\" alt=\"\" \/>&nbsp;&nbsp;<img class=\"tab-image\" style=\"font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-h