oting patterns at the United Nations (UN) on human rights and human security helps identify points of convergence or divergence among the countries of the Atlantic basin with regard to values and approaches to international crises. This paper explores if such countries, or groups of countries within the Atlantic basin, share political concepts and values. Based on four case studies &ndash; Iran, Syria, Haiti and C&ocirc;te d&rsquo;Ivoire &ndash; the paper assesses the similarities and differences regarding conflict resolution and responses to massive human rights violations.<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Download the paper here:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>","views":"297","shares":"0","tweets":"2","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2014-09-29 13:59:00","modified":"2016-02-03 20:36:03"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"72","content_id":"330","type":"1","file_name":"330-ATLANTIC FUTURE_12_Voting patterns in human rights.pdf","description":"Scientific paper no. 12: \u201cAtlantic countries\u2019 voting patterns on human rights and human security at the United Nations\u201d","created":"2014-09-29 14:00:33","modified":"2014-09-29 14:00:33"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"4133","content_id":"330","tag_id":"25","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"25","code":"people-and-institutions","name":"People and institutions","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"EBC635","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:04:26"}},{"id":"4128","content_id":"330","tag_id":"90","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"90","code":"h