d":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"15","code":"south-atlantic","name":"South Atlantic","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:29:49","modified":"2013-09-27 11:29:49"}},{"id":"2682","content_id":"54","tag_id":"53","order":"8","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"53","code":"north-atlantic","name":"North Atlantic","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:53:35","modified":"2013-09-27 11:53:35"}},{"id":"2683","content_id":"54","tag_id":"61","order":"9","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"61","code":"economic-development","name":"Economic development","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 10:48:31","modified":"2013-09-27 10:48:31"}},{"id":"2684","content_id":"54","tag_id":"108","order":"10","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"108","code":"energy","name":"Energy","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:04:45","modified":"2013-09-27 11:04:45"}},{"id":"2685","content_id":"54","tag_id":"126","order":"11","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"126","code":"cooperation","name":"Cooperation","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-30 10:21:56","modified":"2013-09-30 10:21:56"}},{"id":"2686","content_id":"54","tag_id":"129","order":"12","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"129","code":"pacific-area","name":"Pacific area","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-10 11:59:17","modified":"2013-10-10 11:59:17"}},{"id":"2687","content_id":"54","tag_id":"139","order":"13","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"139","code":"asia","name":"Asia","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:20:25","modified":"2013-10-25 10:20:25"}},{"id":"2688","content_id":"54","tag_id":"141","order":"14","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"141","code":"latin-america","name":"Latin America","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:20:43","modified":"2013-10-25 10:20:43"}},{"id":"2689","content_id":"54","tag_id":"143","order":"15","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"143","code":"america","name":"America","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:41:45","modified":"2013-10-25 10:41:45"}},{"id":"2690","content_id":"54","tag_id":"138","order":"16","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"138","code":"europe","name":"Europe","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:16:35","modified":"2013-10-25 10:16:35"}},{"id":"2691","content_id":"54","tag_id":"113","order":"17","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"113","code":"natural-resources","name":"Natural resources","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:08:00","modified":"2013-09-27 11:08:00"}},{"id":"2692","content_id":"54","tag_id":"104","order":"18","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"104","code":"society","name":"Society","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 10:59:47","modified":"2013-09-27 10:59:47"}},{"id":"2693","content_id":"54","tag_id":"170","order":"19","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"170","code":"mexico","name":"Mexico","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2014-01-15 11:11:11","modified":"2014-01-15 11:11:11"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"2694","content_id":"54","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"196","code":"insulza-oas-on-america-in-the-atlantic","user_id":"1","title":"Insulza (OAS) on America in the Atlantic","abstract":"Within the framework of the seminar organized by the ATLANTIC FUTURE, CIDE in Mexico organised a public event with keynote speaker Jos&eacute; Miguel Insulza, Secretary General of the Organization of American States (OAS) under the title &ldquo;America in the Atlantic Space&rdquo;. The conference, open to the public and which attracted a large audience, was held at the National Museum of Anthropology in Mexico City on February 21, 2014.\r\n&nbsp;\r\nSeveral issues concerning the role and the future of Latin America in the wider Atlantic space were discussed, with particular attention to the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (TTIP) between the US and the EU currently under negotiation.","body":"<p>The OAS&nbsp;Secretary General Jos&eacute; Miguel Insulza spoke of the renewal of the Atlantic space and noted that the ATLANTIC FUTURE project is very timely in this context. In recent times, there has been an intellectual and political resurrection of the Atlantic, whose decline was announced prematurely. We are almost used to talk about the Pacific century, he said. Certainly, the rise of Asia is a central phenomenon of our era, but this rise does not occur at the expense of the Atlantic. <strong>The 21st century is not the century of the Pacific but the century of globalization<\/strong>.<\/p>\r\n<p>Insulza noted, as one of the main issues, the <strong>Transatlantic Agreement negotiations on Trade and Investment (TTIP)<\/strong>, which would unite about 50 % of world output and 20% of foreign direct investment if signed. At the same time, he continued, another agreement for the Pacific (TPP) is under negotiation, with 12 countries representing over 38% of world GDP involved. Insulza placed these negotiations in the context of the<strong> emergence of mega - blocks<\/strong>, and noted that these agreements seek to establish new rules that respond to the realities of the 21st century. It is a context of formation of mega-blocks.<\/p>\r\n<p>The Secretary General highlighted the <strong>global value chains as the second major theme in the Atlantic space<\/strong>. He referred to the geographical fragmentation of production, structured in global value chains, and to the fact that the impact on world trade and investment flows are significant. Today, he stressed, the products we receive are \"made in the world&rdquo;. The centre of the value chain will remain where the development of innovation, scientific development and capital is, said Insulza.<\/p>\r\n<p>Insulza referred to Latin America as one of the economic successes of the last decade, but that now faces the risk of not being able to maintain the achievements. They have the challenge of integration into the world economy and its relationship with the mega - blocks as well as the challenge of a more equitable and sustainable growth.<\/p>\r\n<p>He added that export diversification is very important for the Atlantic space in the immediate future. A <strong>greater trade integration of production is needed<\/strong> to reap the benefits of integration. Intraregional trade in Latin America is dominated by trade in final goods. So the challenge may represent a potential transatlantic relations throughout the region. The relationship between the European Union and Latin America has evolved tremendously over the last 30 years. In 2010 Mercosur generated almost half of exports to the European Union. Mexico and Cariforum have a much greater participation in imports from the European Union. There is great potential for growth.<\/p>\r\n<p>Insulza described the fact that most attention goes to Atlantic space because of the start of the negotiations for the TTIP as a great paradox, as this is limited to the more traditional members of the Atlantic Alliance. He warned not to mix the bilateral trade agreement with the creation of a true Atlantic space. <strong>The TTIP is limited to the North Atlantic, but the dialogue should include the rest<\/strong>. Insulza also referred to the importance of South -South relationship. The Secretary- General went on to say that there is a <strong>risk of excluding the South from the dialogue on the Atlantic space<\/strong>. It is time to \"<em>join our voices for a renewed Atlantic space with some cooperation mechanism Atlantic space<\/em>\". In such a framework and voluntarily, Atlantic countries could cooperate on many issues, not only commercial but also environmental and many others.<\/p>\r\n<p>The <strong>emergence of mega - blocks and globalization pose serious challenges<\/strong> for the region. America is the only continent that is Atlantic and Pacific at a time. It could happen that participation in both is possible, or that the label Pacific country or Atlantic country is seen as a new division block.<\/p>\r\n<p>After Jos&eacute; Miguel Isulza speech, a round of questions was opened to the public. Issues such as the negotiation of TTIP, the risks of Mexico looking more towards the Pacific, the key issues for Latin America, or the alleged competition between TPP and TTIP, among others, were addressed.<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>Download the full conference report here:<\/p>","views":"228","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2014-02-27 09:00:00","modified":"2016-02-01 20:13:12"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"54","content_id":"196","type":"1","file_name":"196-C