{"id":"5","code":"atlantic-space","name":"Atlantic space","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 09:55:08","modified":"2013-09-27 09:55:08"}},{"id":"7423","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"137","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"137","code":"european-union","name":"European Union","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:16:06","modified":"2013-10-25 10:16:06"}},{"id":"7424","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"255","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"255","code":"eu-role","name":"eu role","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7425","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"256","order":"5","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"256","code":"values","name":"values","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7426","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"139","order":"6","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"139","code":"asia","name":"Asia","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:20:25","modified":"2013-10-25 10:20:25"}},{"id":"7427","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"186","order":"7","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"186","code":"ttip","name":"ttip","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7428","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"252","order":"8","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"252","code":"north-america","name":"north america","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7429","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"41","order":"9","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"41","code":"actors","name":"Actors","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 09:53:51","modified":"2013-09-27 09:53:51"}},{"id":"7430","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"257","order":"10","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"257","code":"interests","name":"interests","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"7431","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"150","order":"11","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"7432","content_id":"1107","tag_id":"44","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"44","code":"the-atlantic1","name":"The Atlantic","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"0068AD","created":"2013-10-30 14:16:17","modified":"2013-08-02 12:27:19"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"1106","code":"perspectives-from-african-countries","user_id":"1","title":"Perspectives from African countries","abstract":"<p><strong>Four papers present the African perspectives and perceptions on the Atlantic space. The papers expose the results of interviews carried out in Angola, Cameroon, South Africa and West Africa, Morocco, and Cape Verde. <\/strong><\/p>","body":"<p><strong>Perspectives from Angola <\/strong>(by Pedro Seabra, IPRI-UNL)<\/p>\r\n<p>This paper evaluates Angolan perceptions on matters concerning the Atlantic Basin. Through multiple interviews with representatives from a wide spectrum of Angola&rsquo;s society, the main trends, risks and opportunities in this area are explored while the role of norms and values, cooperation and regionalism as potential drivers of further relations are weighted in and evaluated. Ultimately, the paper addresses the main question of knowing whether or not Angola perceives new dynamics in the Atlantic as existent and\/or desirable and reflects on what role the country might play in the long run in such kind of regional scenario.<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Perspectives from Cameroon, South Africa and West Africa <\/strong>(by&nbsp;Frank Mattheis,&nbsp;Centre for the Study of Governance Innovation, University of Pretoria)<\/p>\r\n<p>This paper studies how selected experts from West Africa, Cameroon and South Africa assess the potential of an emerging Atlantic space. Covering representatives from various sectors in society, the analysed interviews reveal how divergence and convergence is perceived in terms of economics, institutions, energy and security. The findings reveal a very cautious approach to the idea of an Atlantic space. The priorities of political imaginations appear to be centred on national interests and on the rise of Asia in the global order, leaving very little excitement for a project with regions that are either seen as dominant (Europe and North America) or unknown (South America). The strengthening of an Atlantic identity and of a potential Pan-Atlantic institution will therefore require a decided change of perception among the targeted actors in West Africa, Cameroon and South Africa towards the other Atlantic regions. &nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Perspectives from Morocco&nbsp;<\/strong>(by&nbsp;Sqalli Hammad, HEM-CESEM)<\/p>\r\n<p>This paper presents Moroccan perspectives and perceptions of the construction of a pan-Atlantic space. Findings are based on 20 interviews covering 4 thematic areas: economy and finance, security, people and institutions, resources and environment. They show the multileveled complexity of the issues at hand and the near absence of a vision of the Atlantic. Nevertheless, emergent initiatives are not counteracting an Atlantic will. Moroccans are not anywhere near an Atlantic project aimed at integrating economies and people; domestic issues and new African perspective seem to take precedence over an immediate pan-Atlantic configuration.<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Perspectives from Cape Verde<\/strong> (Katarina Pereira da Costa, HEM-CESEM)<\/p>\r\n<p>The interviews were carried out in Cape Verde using a standardised questionnaire developed by the Atlantic Future project. The interviewee&rsquo;s were people (of both genders) from the public sector, private sector, academia, media and civil society and the interviews covered the thematic areas of economy and finance, security, people and institutions and resources and environment subject of study of the Atlantic Future project. Most interviewees perceived a pan-Atlantic space taking shape or at least they expressed their desire that it could emerge would be happening. They saw a movement towards cooperation especially in economics and security. Many suggestions were made on how to stimulate the creation of a pan-Atlantic space by those who did not forseen a pan-Atlantic taking shape yet or whom believed it is still a very insignificant movement.<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Download the four papers here:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>","views":"151","shares":"0","tweets":"0","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2015-10-05 09:26:00","modified":"2016-02-07 08:07:16"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"138","content_id":"1106","type":"1","file_name":"1106-ATLANTIC FUTURE_WP7_Perspectives from Angola.pdf","description":"Perspectives from Angola, by Pedro Seabra, IPRI-UNL","created":"2015-09-08