tentTag":{"id":"5296","content_id":"450","tag_id":"21","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"21","code":"security","name":"Security","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"C31F4A","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:37"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"373","code":"food-security-in-the-atlantic","user_id":"1","title":"FOOD SECURITY IN THE ATLANTIC","abstract":"<p>ATLANTIC FUTURE scientific paper no. 19 is out: \"Food security and agriculture issues in the Atlantic Basin&rdquo;, by&nbsp;Omar Aloui&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/www.cesem.ma\/\">HEM-CESEM<\/a>.&nbsp;<\/p>","body":"<p>Uncertainties about world markets&nbsp;<em>reliability<\/em><em>&nbsp;<\/em>and food production systems&nbsp;<em>sustainability<\/em>have renewed the interest on alternative cooperation arenas and agendas aiming to improve food security, in particular for developing countries. This paper explores food and agricultural issues in the Atlantic Basin from this perspective. It presents a synthesis of food security&nbsp;<em>global debates<\/em><em>&nbsp;<\/em>in relation to agriculture. It gives a strategic analysis of main Atlantic regions based on their current food security situation and their agricultural growth potential. It concludes by recognizing possible contributions of Atlantic Basin to global food security. It identifies&nbsp;<em>public goods investments<\/em><em>&nbsp;<\/em>in the Atlantic Basin for which feasibility studies are fully justified (reserves,&nbsp;logistics, health and environment). It may the case for&nbsp;<em>value adding<\/em><em>&nbsp;<\/em>South-South transatlantic cooperation and vertical African integration initiatives that should be expanded.<\/p>","views":"394","shares":"0","tweets":"2","mails":"1","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2014-10-08 14:21:00","modified":"2016-02-08 08:03:00"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"90","content_id":"373","type":"1","file_name":"373-ATLANTIC FUTURE_19_Food security.compressed.pdf","description":"Scientific paper no. 19: \"Food security and agriculture issues in the Atlantic Basin\"","created":"2014-10-09 10:06:22","modified":"2014-10-09 10:06:22"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"4087","content_id":"373","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},{"id":"4080","content_id":"373","tag_id":"163","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"163","code":"food-security","name":"food security","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"4081","content_id":"373","tag_id":"26","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},{"id":"4082","content_id":"373","tag_id":"126","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"126","code":"cooperation","name":"Cooperation","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-30 10:21:56","modified":"2013-09-30 10:21:56"}},{"id":"4083","content_id":"373","tag_id":"140","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"140","code":"africa","name":"Africa","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-10-25 10:20:33","modified":"2013-10-25 10:20:33"}},{"id":"4084","content_id":"373","tag_id":"15","order":"5","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"15","code":"south-atlantic","name":"South Atlantic","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:29:49","modified":"2013-09-27 11:29:49"}},{"id":"4085","content_id":"373","tag_id":"243","order":"6","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"243","code":"agriculture","name":"agriculture","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"4086","content_id":"373","tag_id":"150","order":"7","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"4087","content_id":"373","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"339","code":"atlantic-basin-green-policy-index","user_id":"1","title":"Atlantic Basin Green Policy Index","abstract":"<p><strong>ATLANTIC FUTURE scientific paper no. 18 is out: \"<\/strong><strong>Sustainable Policy Perceptions in the Atlantic Basin Green Policy Index<\/strong><strong>\", by <\/strong><strong>Marina Drummond<\/strong><strong> at&nbsp;<\/strong><strong><a href=\"http:\/\/portal.fgv.br\/\">Funda&ccedil;&atilde;o Getulio Vargas<\/a><\/strong><\/p>","body":"<p>The Green Policy Index works with the premise that policymakers would benefit from a clearer outline of the perception of those working in the sustainability field. It aims to examine perception of governmental policy-openness, likely timescales for policy implementation and perceived attitudes towards potential environmental harm. By mapping out the views of people who work closely with sustainability issues in Atlantic Basin countries, we consider that it is possible to gauge how favourable - as regards principle - and\/or cautious - as regards&nbsp;implementation &ndash; Basin countries are to environmental policy options. Environmental concerns are likely to increase in the future and those who have not had the forethought to invest in sustainability will be faced with ever smaller margins of flexibility. Depending upon how intensively and collectively - or not - sustainability policies are implemented, relations between Atlantic Basin countries will gradually become either conflictual or synergistic. From the GPI&nbsp;we intend to determine the potential roadblocks and points of contention that ought to be considered in the drawing board phase of green policy planning for the Atlantic Basin as a whole. It ought to be noted, however, that although we are working with the hypothesis that the polling of SD experts on sustainable policies will yield useful material, this research should be viewed as a pilot investigation into the desirability of producing the GPI on a more regular basis.&nbsp;In short, we aim to discover whether it is possible to collect and present useful information on green policy by polling SD experts, and, if so, whether various stakeholders would support the development and\/or deployment of an annual survey to capture the full spectrum of green policy perception.<\/p>","views":"361","shares":"0","tweets":"1","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2014-09-29 15:09:00","modified":"2016-01-31 09:41:31"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"97","content_id":"339","type":"1","file_name":"339-ATLANTIC FUTURE_18_Sustainable Policy Perceptions in the Atlantic Basin.compressed.pdf","description":"Sustainable Policy Perceptions in the Atlantic Basin","created":"2014-12-05 14:26:04","modified":"2014-12-05 14:26:04"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"4246","content_id":"339","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},{"id":"4241","content_id":"339","tag_id":"43","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"43","code":"policy","name":"Policy","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 10:04:43","modified":"2013-09-27 10:04:43"}},{"id":"4242","content_id":"339","tag_id":"109","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"109","code":"environment","name":"Environment","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:06:53","modified":"2013-09-27 11:06:53"}},{"id":"4243","content_id":"339","tag_id":"167","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"167","code":"fundacao-getulio-vargas-fgv-rio-de-janeiro","name":"funda\u00e7ao get\u00falio vargas (fgv) rio de janeiro","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"4244","content_id":"339","tag_id":"168","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"168","code":"-brazil","name":" brazil","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"4245","content_id":"339","tag_id":"150","order":"5","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"4246","content_id":"339","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"338","code":"an-atlantic-energy-renaissance","user_id":"1","title":"An Atlantic energy renaissance","abstract":"<p><strong>ATLANTIC FUTURE scientific paper no. 17 is out: \"<\/strong><strong>Atlantic Energy and the Changing Global Energy Flow Map<\/strong><strong>\", by <\/strong><strong>Paul Isbell<\/strong><strong>&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>at&nbsp;<\/strong><strong><a href=\"http:\/\/transatlantic.sais-jhu.edu\/\">CTR<\/a>&nbsp;<\/strong>(<strong>Center for Transatlantic Relations at Johns Hopkins University's School of Advanced International Studies)<\/strong><\/p>","body":"<p>An &lsquo;Atlantic energy renaissance&rsquo; is currently unfolding across the &lsquo;Atlantic Basin,&rsquo; where roughly half of the world&rsquo;s known fossil fuels are located and more than two-thirds of the world&rsquo;s renewable energy is currently generated. The technological revolutions in &lsquo;unconventional&rsquo; and &lsquo;difficult&rsquo; hydrocarbons &ndash; in shale and offshore &ndash; have recently contributed to a shift in the global center of gravity of energy supply away from the &lsquo;Great Crescent&rsquo; and into the &lsquo;Atlantic Basin.&rsquo; Combined with the shift in the global center of gravity for demand to emerging Asia-Pacific, these &lsquo;revolutions&rsquo; are reversing the traditional &lsquo;westward&rsquo; flow of energy from Eurasia to the Atlantic to produce a new pattern of global flows in which the countries of the Atlantic Basin will increasingly become the net suppliers of energy at the margin to Asia-Pacific. Furthermore, such &lsquo;revolutions&rsquo; have also played a role in the recent reversal of fortunes of renewable energy, particularly in the Northern Atlantic. Therefore, while shifting energy flow map &ndash; largely driven by the Atlantic energy renaissance &ndash; both calls into question the notion of the &lsquo;Asian century&rsquo; and problematizes the rationale behind the US &lsquo;pivot to Asia,&rsquo; it also reveals new geopolitical and governance potential along the strategic horizon for Atlantic actors. However, such potential&nbsp;will remain unrealized without &lsquo;pan-Atlantic energy cooperation that addresses both the emerging issues of the new &lsquo;energy seascape&rsquo; and the low carbon &lsquo;imperative.&rsquo; Finally, the &lsquo;Atlantic energy renaissance&rsquo; and the changing global energy flow map of which it is both cause and effect, also highlights the growing relative strategic significance of the &lsquo;Southern Atlantic&rsquo;.<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Download the paper here:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>","views":"1090","shares":"0","tweets":"1","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2014-09-29 15:06:00","modified":"2016-02-08 16:04:31"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"77","content_id":"338","type":"1","file_name":"338-ATLANTIC FUTURE_17_Energy.pdf","description":"Scientific paper no. 17: \u201cAtlantic Energy and the Changing Global Energy Flow Map\u201d","created":"2014-09-29 15:08:02","modified":"2014-09-29 15:08:02"}],"ContentTag":[{"id":"4101","content_id":"338","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},{"id":"4094","content_id":"338","tag_id":"108","order":"1","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"108","code":"energy","name":"Energy","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:04:45","modified":"2013-09-27 11:04:45"}},{"id":"4095","content_id":"338","tag_id":"162","order":"2","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"162","code":"resources","name":"resources","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":null,"created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"}},{"id":"4096","content_id":"338","tag_id":"1","order":"3","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"1","code":"atlantic-basin","name":"Atlantic Basin","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 09:54:32","modified":"2013-09-27 09:54:32"}},{"id":"4097","content_id":"338","tag_id":"126","order":"4","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"126","code":"cooperation","name":"Cooperation","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-30 10:21:56","modified":"2013-09-30 10:21:56"}},{"id":"4098","content_id":"338","tag_id":"125","order":"5","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"125","code":"johns-hopkins-university-jhu","name":"Johns Hopkins University (JHU)","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-30 10:19:12","modified":"2013-09-30 10:19:12"}},{"id":"4099","content_id":"338","tag_id":"15","order":"6","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"15","code":"south-atlantic","name":"South Atlantic","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"FFFFFF","created":"2013-09-27 11:29:49","modified":"2013-09-27 11:29:49"}},{"id":"4100","content_id":"338","tag_id":"150","order":"7","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","Tag":{"id":"150","code":"results","name":"Results","type":"0","mandatory":false,"color":"#FFFFFF","created":"2013-12-11 13:44:03","modified":"2013-12-10 14:14:40"}}],"MainCategory":{"ContentTag":{"id":"4101","content_id":"338","tag_id":"26","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"26","code":"resources-and-environment","name":"Resources and environment","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"9AC4AB","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:22"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"337","code":"climate-change-impacts-in-the-atlantic","user_id":"1","title":"Climate change impacts in the Atlantic","abstract":"<blockquote><strong>[Photo Credit: Reuters File Photo]<\/strong><\/blockquote>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>ATLANTIC FUTURE scientific paper no. 16 is out: \"<\/strong><strong>Climate change impacts in the Atlantic Basin and coordinated adaptation responses<\/strong><strong>\", by <\/strong><strong>Christoph Stefes, Andrew Reid, Lucy Smith, and Elizabeth Tedsen<\/strong><strong> at&nbsp;<\/strong><a href=\"http:\/\/www.ecologic.eu\/\">Ecologic Institute<\/a><\/p>","body":"<p>The need for ambitious implementation of strategies and measures for climate adaptation has become clear, however, at a global level, it is uncertain if or whether the issue is best confronted by centralised or fragmented structures of adaptation governance. This paper, an output of the EU ATLANTIC FUTURE project, investigates the dynamic network of transnational climate adaptation institutions currently working in the Atlantic Basin region. From a broad pool of adaptation institutions present in the Atlantic, eight case studies were selected and investigated, together representing an array of regions, forms of cooperation, actors, and thematic issues. Through case study analysis, this paper considers whether the work undertaken by these institutions is uniquely &lsquo;Atlantic&rsquo; in nature &ndash; that is, if and how they are driven, facilitated, or bounded by the specific actors, climate impacts, or characteristics of the region &ndash; or whether they are more global in nature. Secondly, we examine how these institutions fit within the larger picture of fragmented global climate adaptation governance. In doing so, we find indications that the Atlantic hosts and fosters a diverse and active array of institutions, but that these are largely focused on the production and exchange of scientific knowledge and capacity building, rather than on the implementation of concrete measures. Although the fragmented governance structure currently in place has produced much valuable work, increased centralisation could be beneficial for ensuring better coordination and implementation of adaptation activities at the ground level.<\/p>\r\n<p><strong>Download the paper here:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>","views":"630","shares":"0","tweets":"2","mails":"0","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2014-09-29 15:03:00","modified":"2016-02-07 05:16:14"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Administrator","last_name":null,"password":"c8d482e69d7de06cc7429d3b9484c8145fdfb818","code":"","role":"0","type":"0","published":true,"created":"2014-06-26 10:44:32","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Event":{"id":null,"datetime":null,"country":null,"city":null,"address":null,"map":null},"Resource":[{"id":"76","content_id":"337","type":"1","file_name":"337-ATLANTIC FUTURE_16_Climate change impacts in the Atlantic Basin.pdf","description":"Scientific paper