tTag":{"id":"5296","content_id":"450","tag_id":"21","order":"0","created":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","modified":"0000-00-00 00:00:00"},"Tag":{"id":"21","code":"security","name":"Security","type":"1","mandatory":true,"color":"C31F4A","created":"2013-10-21 17:29:28","modified":"2013-09-27 10:08:37"}},"Format":[]},{"Content":{"id":"373","code":"food-security-in-the-atlantic","user_id":"1","title":"FOOD SECURITY IN THE ATLANTIC","abstract":"<p>ATLANTIC FUTURE scientific paper no. 19 is out: \"Food security and agriculture issues in the Atlantic Basin&rdquo;, by&nbsp;Omar Aloui&nbsp;at&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/www.cesem.ma\/\">HEM-CESEM<\/a>.&nbsp;<\/p>","body":"<p>Uncertainties about world markets&nbsp;<em>reliability<\/em><em>&nbsp;<\/em>and food production systems&nbsp;<em>sustainability<\/em>have renewed the interest on alternative cooperation arenas and agendas aiming to improve food security, in particular for developing countries. This paper explores food and agricultural issues in the Atlantic Basin from this perspective. It presents a synthesis of food security&nbsp;<em>global debates<\/em><em>&nbsp;<\/em>in relation to agriculture. It gives a strategic analysis of main Atlantic regions based on their current food security situation and their agricultural growth potential. It concludes by recognizing possible contributions of Atlantic Basin to global food security. It identifies&nbsp;<em>public goods investments<\/em><em>&nbsp;<\/em>in the Atlantic Basin for which feasibility studies are fully justified (reserves,&nbsp;logistics, health and environment). It may the case for&nbsp;<em>value adding<\/em><em>&nbsp;<\/em>South-South transatlantic cooperation and vertical African integration initiatives that should be expanded.<\/p>","views":"394","shares":"0","tweets":"2","mails":"1","published":true,"image":true,"featured":true,"type":"0","created":"2014-10-08 14:21:00","modified":"2016-02-08 08:03:00"},"User":{"id":"1","email":"info@onebigrobot.com","first_name":"Adminis